This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it focuses on improving communication reliability in cognitive networks. It also involves the use of cloud-based relays, which is a common topic in networking research. 

It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it proposes an algorithm to improve the minimum outage probability for communication reliability. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as communication reliability is a crucial aspect of secure communication. 

It may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the optimization of relay selection algorithms to improve system performance. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it involves the use of algorithms and simulations to improve communication reliability.
